./configure --with-single-user --with-booby --disable-libavc1394 --disable-libiec61883 --disable-libtheora --disable-tiff --disable-dav1d --without-ladspa --without-firewire --without-nv

make

[it will fail at some point]

cp /usr/share/automake-1.16/config.guess thirdparty/a52dec-0.7.4/autotools/
cp /usr/share/automake-1.16/config.guess thirdparty/libogg-1.3.4/
cp /usr/share/automake-1.16/config.guess thirdparty/libdv-1.0.0/
cp /usr/share/automake-1.16/config.guess thirdparty/libuuid-1.0.3/
cp /usr/share/automake-1.16/config.guess thirdparty/libtheora-1.1.1/
cp /usr/share/automake-1.16/config.guess thirdparty/ladspa-0.4.17/

there might be better way of doing this:
https://github.com/easybuilders/easybuild-easyblocks/issues/1276
autoreconf && automake --add-missing --copy --force-missing &&
short form of automake must be 'automake -caf'

so full version will be

autoreconf -ifv && automake -caf

try to add this to thirdparty/Makefile
to proga.var= variable 


# force reconfigure/rebuild
rm thirdparty/build/libogg.configure

do the same for each tree needing autoreconf

 autoreconf -ifv

in

thirdparty/a52dec-0.7.4/
thirdparty/libogg-1.3.4/
thirdparty/libdv-1.0.0/
thirdparty/libuuid-1.0.3/
thirdparty/ladspa-0.4.17/

run
autoreconf -fiv -I m4

in libtheora-1.1.1


apply from thirparty/

cat ../LIBOGG_configure_ac_fix.diff | patch -p0

cat ../MJPEGTOOLS_disable_sse2.diff | patch -p0

cat ../LAME_no_see.diff | patch

# yeah I did it backward
cat ../OPENEXR_2.4.1_no_see_no_x86.diff | patch -R -p0

cat ../X264_no_sse2.diff | patch -p


in
 thirdparty/x264-snapshot-20191217-2245-stable

fix configure (not real autotools script)

then return to top of the tree and hit make

make will stop at each build error, but because build is parallel
exact error may scroll out of view. rerun make :}



Do not forgot to run 'make install' even for single-user build

resulting relocateable binary tree must be in bin/
